0
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:22,598
- I knew you'd come back.
- Piper.

1
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:24,557
Phoebe was worried,
Prue was a wreck,

2
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:26,119
but I knew you'd find a way.

3
00:00:26,320 --> 00:00:27,435
We need to talk.

4
00:00:27,920 --> 00:00:29,353
Leo, you haven't kissed me
in a week.

5
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:31,476
Don't you think maybe
that takes priority?

6
00:00:42,280 --> 00:00:44,840
- I came to say goodbye.
- What?

7
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,833
They told us to break up.
They caught us trying to get married.

8
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:50,998
So we won't get married. We'll wait.

9
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:52,919
It's too late, we broke the rules.

10
00:00:53,080 --> 00:00:54,957
Now they won't let us
see each other again.

11
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,037
Wait a minute. They won't what?

12
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,474
I don't care what they do to me,

13
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:02,995
but I couldn't bear
anything happening to you.

14
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:05,116
I shouldn't even be here right now.

15
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:08,792
Wait a minute. Leo, I can't hear you.
What are you saying?

16
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:11,076
You have to forget about me.

17
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:15,391
Leo.

18
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:18,231
I love you.

19
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,591
Leo!

20
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:31,511
Leo!

21
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,319
Piper.

22
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:36,072
Piper.

23
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:38,350
Piper, wake up!

24
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:40,238
Piper.

25
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:47,790
Leo's not coming back.

26
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:52,671
Honey, it was just a bad dream.

27
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:54,994
No, it wasn't.

28
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,310
It was real.

29
00:01:58,040 --> 00:02:00,349
I don't understand.

30
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,755
Why are they doing this to us?

31
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:06,555
It's like destroying lives is how
they amuse themselves.

32
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,558
Piper, watch what you say.

33
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:11,194
Why? What are they
gonna do to me?

34
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:14,511
They couldn't hurt me more
than they already have.

35
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,755
Don't you just love cell phones.

36
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,393
Hey, it's me.

37
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:35,070
It's amazing how much stress you can
project with so few words, Prue.

38
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:37,595
I will have your precious car
home momentarily.

39
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:40,758
Phoebe, I am not calling about the car,
I'm calling about Piper.

40
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,592
Look...

41
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:44,432
...she had this dream about Leo.

42
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:47,353
And maybe I'm overreacting,
but I've never seen her like this.

43
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:50,239
It's... It's like she's
completely given up.

44
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,953
What kind of dream about Leo?

45
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,469
Phoebe?

46
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:58,790
I'm fine, the car's fine,
I'll see you later, bye.

47
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,633
Hi. Are you okay?

48
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,997
You can't have it!
Leave me alone!

49
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,838
I won't give it to you!
Leave me alone!

50
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:33,114
It's okay, it's okay.
You're safe. You're safe.

51
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:31,471
Okay.

52
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:35,952
You just have to be very careful
because it's hot, so blow on it, okay?

53
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:38,429
Hey, did you find out
anything more from her?

54
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:40,193
Name, rank and serial number.

55
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:44,279
Her parents are on the way,
they live up the street.

56
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:46,908
They were very worried about you.

57
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:49,590
I'm gonna go to the car
and get her jacket.

58
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,876
- Keys?
- What?

59
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:54,435
You know, silver shiny things
that go jingle-jingle?

60
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:56,073
I don't have them.

61
00:04:56,760 --> 00:04:59,274
That's so weird.
I put them up here.

62
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,952
The fairies probably hid them.

63
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,952
What was that?

64
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:09,192
Sorry. I'm not supposed
to talk about fairies.

65
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:14,519
You know what? In this house,
you can talk about anything you want.

66
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:17,399
Sometimes we talk about
weird things too.

67
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,869
Well, that's what fairies do.

68
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,951
Hide your keys and things.

69
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,718
They're tricky like that.

70
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:28,029
Is that what's in that box?

71
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:30,195
Is it a fairy?

72
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,953
Is that who you're protecting?

73
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:38,192
That's probably your
mom and your dad.

74
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:40,154
He's not my dad.

75
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:42,914
He's just my mom's new husband.

76
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:49,195
- Hi, we're Kate's parents.
- Is she all right?

77
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:52,039
Yeah, she's fine. I mean,
she scraped her arm a little bit,

78
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,753
but mostly she's just scared.

79
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,069
Kate?

80
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,635
- Get out of the doorway.
- Kate.

81
00:05:57,840 --> 00:06:00,229
It's an in-between.
Get out of the in-between.

82
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,677
- What's an in-between?
- Where the trolls are.

83
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:08,077
Honey, we've had
this conversation before.

84
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:12,229
You're a big girl, and it's time to stop
believing in things like that.

85
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:18,712
She's had some problems
since her father and I divorced.

86
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:22,917
Regressed, sort of,
back to the imaginary-friends stage.

87
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:25,714
Look, we should go. It's late.

88
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:28,679
Thank you again, for everything.

89
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,839
They'll get us.

90
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:33,592
I won't let them.

91
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,631
It's okay.

92
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,677
Look, there it is!

93
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,950
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

94
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:06,236
Come on, Phoebe, trolls and fairies?
You don't believe that stuff.

95
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:08,311
Sure, why not?

96
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:11,398
Well, maybe it's time
we tell her about Santa.

97
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:14,599
All I know is something
was definitely after her.

98
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,994
But you didn't see anything?

99
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,918
No, but how else did she get hurt?

100
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:20,395
How about she fell down
and scratched herself?

101
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:23,398
No, Piper, they weren't scratches,
they were claw marks.

102
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,194
If they were, you would have seen
what had clawed her.

103
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,952
Why are you being
so stubborn about this?

104
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,957
Because I'm a Scorpio,
what's your excuse?

105
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:35,113
Okay, so it's kind of late,
and we're all a little bit tired.

106
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,793
So how about we finish
this up tomorrow?

107
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:39,918
Now look what you did. You went
and turned Prue into the middle child.

108
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:42,514
Okay, Phoebe.
Even if fairies and trolls do exist,

109
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:43,795
you heard what her mom said.

110
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,552
The problem started
when her father left.

111
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,839
- That's psychology, not magic.
- I know.

112
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,719
But you know what? I'm gonna check
the Book of Shadows, just in case.

113
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:54,758
Because I don't want to be
out-stubborned by a Gemini.

114
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,317
No, don't! The tweens!

115
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:11,351
They come out of the shadows.

116
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:15,718
Honey, just go to sleep, okay?

117
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,631
Please.

118
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,473
Go away.

119
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:33,158
Leave us alone.

120
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,472
Hey.

121
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:49,518
Check this out.

122
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:52,039
We each drew one.

123
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,191
- "Lily."
- Do you remember her?

124
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:56,828
She was our little imaginary friend
we had when we were kids.

125
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:59,630
I have not thought about Lily
in years.

126
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:02,912
That's because you grew up,
and you stopped seeing her.

127
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:05,478
Okay.

128
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:08,188
Fairies, elves and trolls
are mystical creatures

129
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:13,673
that live in a realm parallel to ours,
but separated by a thin veil.

130
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:15,831
The Enchanted Realm?

131
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:20,278
A thin veil which lifts only
in tween places. Tween places, Prue.

132
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:23,313
That's like a realm
in between two things.

133
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:26,193
Like doorways and windows,
shadows.

134
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,868
- Shadows?
- In between light and dark.

135
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:32,117
And It's exactly what Kate said,
trolls live in the in-between.

136
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,959
Right, but when you found Kate,
she wasn't in an in-between.

137
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:38,756
Actually, she was in the biggest
in-between of all: midnight.

138
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:42,475
"In the hour between night and day,
the world itself becomes a tween."

139
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:45,319
Okay, so why isn't there anything
in the Book of Shadows?

140
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,715
Because the Book of Shadows
was written by adults.

141
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:53,153
And I'm assuming that scary-Iooking
dude in your picture is a troll.

142
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:55,835
So then why is he trying
to hurt Kate?

143
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,477
I don't know, we have to ask Kate.

144
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:01,154
And we will fill Piper in on the way.

145
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:03,715
You know, maybe we should
just do this one on our own.

146
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,797
I mean, Piper's kind of out of it.

147
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:09,037
Even more reason to drag her along,
take her mind off of Leo.

148
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,270
Phoebe, phone!

149
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:19,832
- It's your little lawyer boyfriend.
- So there.

150
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,116
- And he is not my boyfriend.
- Weird.

151
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:25,113
- Hello?
- Who's not your boyfriend?

152
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:28,350
The mailman.

153
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:31,549
Yeah, sometimes Piper
likes to tease me

154
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:34,678
because I like to get the mail a lot.

155
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:36,239
So how are you?

156
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:40,228
Well, it's a beautiful morning and
I got a beautiful woman on the phone,

157
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:42,675
so things could be worse.

158
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,390
God, I sound like Billy Appleby.

159
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:48,914
- What?
- Nothing.

160
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,917
No, wait, what did you just say?

161
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:54,399
Billy Appleby is just this
hokey guy from this old movie

162
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:56,710
I watched too many times
when I was a kid.

163
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:58,319
Kill it Before it Dies.

164
00:10:58,520 --> 00:11:00,795
- You've seen it?
- Once or twice.

165
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:01,949
Really?

166
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:05,235
Too bad it's not playing,
I'd take you to see it.

167
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,594
I love you.

168
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,910
Course we could always
have dinner instead.

169
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:11,190
Are you asking me out, counsellor?

170
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,277
Guilty.

171
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,672
How about tonight?

172
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:18,108
I could stop by your place.

173
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:20,591
Really? Well...

174
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:24,639
Actually tonight's not good because
Piper is going through something.

175
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:28,190
But I will call you and maybe we could
meet at the club, okay?

176
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,118
Sorry, bye.

177
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:45,515
Did you not look at those drawings?

178
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:46,829
They're cute, yes.

179
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,673
Cute? Cute?

180
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:51,189
We all had the same
invisible fairy friend, Piper.

181
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:53,476
That is proof that fairies exist.

182
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:55,794
Or...

183
00:11:56,840 --> 00:12:00,958
...it proves that one of us
had a really fertile imagination,

184
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,395
and the other two
were really good copycats.

185
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:08,031
Okay, Piper, honey,
just listen to me, okay?

186
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:11,118
We think that Kate's in trouble.
Our kind of trouble.

187
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:13,473
Okay, well I don't.

188
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:15,232
And after what they did to Leo,

189
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:18,676
I'm not really all that motivated
to go dig up demons for them.

190
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:20,793
- Trolls.
- Whatever.

191
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:23,594
Look, you guys can do
whatever you want,

192
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:25,876
but I've had it, and I'm done.

193
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:31,716
- What does that mean?
- That means that the powers that be

194
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:34,075
haven't done anything
but ruin my life,

195
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:37,437
so therefore I'm not gonna do anything
for them anymore, okay?

196
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:41,513
I'm going now.
Excuse me. I'm going now.

197
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:47,030
I think she's on strike.

198
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:04,479
Kate, someone's here to see you.

199
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,593
Hey.

200
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:19,435
So we brought you your jacket.

201
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,630
We had to use the spare key
to get into the car, though.

202
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,717
I guess the fairies hid them after all.

203
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,115
Told you.

204
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:30,158
What are you drawing?
That looks like a very scary cave.

205
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:35,198
You know, that looks a lot like mine.

206
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,918
That's a fairy and a troll.

207
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:39,793
My mom says I'm making them up,
but I'm not.

208
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:44,397
We believe you.

209
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:47,717
We just need you to tell us everything
that you know so we can help.

210
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,479
I don't know that much.

211
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:51,517
Thistle's kind of hard to understand.

212
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:53,671
Fairies don't talk the same way
people do.

213
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,514
- Thistle?
- I saved her.

214
00:13:57,680 --> 00:14:00,240
See, the fairies are the bosses
of the enchanted kingdom,

215
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,311
but the trolls wish
they were the bosses.

216
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:05,278
So they kidnapped Thistle from
the king and queen of the fairies.

217
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:07,398
So Thistle is a princess?

218
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:12,315
But the trolls are gonna kill her unless
her parents hand over the kingdom.

219
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:14,279
It's a miniature coup d'état.

220
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:17,833
But I found her tied up in a cave
and I saved her.

221
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,878
That was very brave of you.

222
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:23,353
But now the trolls hate me
because I won't give her back.

223
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:26,114
Most of the time, I can stay out
of the in-betweens,

224
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:28,919
- but at midnight...
- There's no place to hide.

225
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:30,838
Yeah, we know.

226
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:33,920
Can we see her?

227
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:37,478
No, only children can see fairies.

228
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,997
Well, I don't know if this
is gonna help at all,

229
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:44,392
but Prue and I, we're very in touch
with our inner children.

230
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,433
Can we at least try?

231
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:51,556
We'll have to go into an in-between.

232
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:53,358
Watch out for trolls.

233
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:55,398
Okay.

234
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,199
Can't help if you can't see her.

235
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:27,511
Thistle says that if you
really believe in fairies,

236
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:31,355
there's something that'll make you
innocent again so you can see them.

237
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:48,873
I think it worked.

238
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,839
I wanna see the fairy.

239
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:23,036
If you're happy and you know it
Clap your hands

240
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:27,472
If you're happy and you know it
Pat your knee

241
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:29,159
Oh, my God.

242
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:31,471
- Pat your knee
- You guys gotta do it.

243
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:35,434
If you're happy and you know it
Then your face will surely show it

244
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,919
If you're happy and you...

245
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:39,469
- What the hell is going on?
- You think this is bad?

246
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:41,676
You should have been here
for "Frere Jacques."

247
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:44,394
They've been acting like kids
since they got here.

248
