490
00:32:20,680 --> 00:32:22,796
Oh, Prue, I am focusing,
believe me.

491
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:25,878
You're too upset, so take
a deep breath and try again.

492
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:28,110
I can't levitate when I want to,
I can't premonition...

493
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:29,918
- Guys!
- What?

494
00:32:30,320 --> 00:32:32,788
I think the spell is working.

495
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:43,838
Do you see it?

496
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:46,477
What's it doing?

497
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:49,108
I think it wants us to follow it.

498
00:33:12,120 --> 00:33:14,076
I think he got scared away.

499
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:16,999
Yeah, and I can see why. This looks
like the cave from Kate's drawing.

500
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:20,673
First troll I see is in really big trouble.
Let's go.

501
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:38,755
Troll central.

502
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:50,399
- What are they doing?
- Looks like they're trying to start a fire,

503
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:53,160
although I don't really think
that it's for roasting marshmallows.

504
00:33:53,360 --> 00:33:54,588
Kate and Thistle.

505
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:05,629
Piper, do you think that you can
freeze them from here?

506
00:34:05,840 --> 00:34:07,239
I can try.

507
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,436
- Piper, freeze them!
- They're too fast.

508
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:25,190
- One down.
- Oh, Kate!

509
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,913
Okay.

510
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,077
- Prue, a little help here!
- Okay.

511
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,436
- Piper, run.
- Run? Run where?

512
00:34:42,120 --> 00:34:43,792
- Piper, run!
- Are you out of your mind?

513
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:45,632
Freeze the flames!

514
00:34:47,520 --> 00:34:48,953
Unfreeze. Now.

515
00:34:53,720 --> 00:34:56,996
Now, that is just the way I like
my trolls, medium well.

516
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:03,590
Hi. Here you guys go.

517
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:04,795
It's okay.

518
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:06,678
There you go.

519
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:09,790
Hey. Hey, you guys, wait up!

520
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:14,597
Thistle, don't you know how to turn
Kate back into a person?

521
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:18,748
Kate, you know,
you can't stay a fairy,

522
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:21,593
because if you do,
your mom will be very sad.

523
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:28,835
You know what?

524
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:31,753
I think I kind of know
how you're feeling.

525
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:33,672
When someone you love
goes away,

526
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:37,515
it doesn't make any sense, and you feel
like the whole world is out to get you.

527
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:39,559
But you know what?

528
00:35:39,760 --> 00:35:42,320
Your mom and dad
didn't split up to hurt you.

529
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:44,796
Things just happen.

530
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:47,872
Things that you may
never understand.

531
00:35:48,160 --> 00:35:51,391
But you just have to believe
that it's for the best.

532
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:53,511
Even if it doesn't always
seem that way.

533
00:35:56,880 --> 00:35:59,519
You remember how sad you were
when your daddy left?

534
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:05,517
Well, that's how sad everybody's
gonna be if you don't come home.

535
00:36:25,080 --> 00:36:26,877
Nicely done.

536
00:36:37,640 --> 00:36:38,675
Yep.

537
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:40,990
- Ice?
- Bed.

538
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:54,076
Who delivers at this hour?

539
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:03,190
I think that this is someone's way
of saying thank you.

540
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:07,278
- Oh, here.
- Thank you.

541
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:09,476
Well, you're welcome.

542
00:37:10,200 --> 00:37:12,509
Oh, they're so pretty.

543
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,996
Piper, we...

544
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:24,998
We...

545
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:26,918
- We just...
- I know.

546
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:28,348
It's okay.

547
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:30,112
I'm actually beginning to understand

548
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:33,829
why they don't want witches
and whitelighters to be together.

549
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:43,118
Marriage is hard enough, you know.

550
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:49,189
But marriage to a whitelighter...

551
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:53,037
He's gotta orb out
at all times of the night.

552
00:37:53,200 --> 00:37:56,351
And sometimes he's gone
for weeks at a time.

553
00:37:58,600 --> 00:38:00,909
But honestly,
if I'm gonna have a meltdown

554
00:38:01,080 --> 00:38:04,152
every time I have no idea
where he is...

555
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:07,508
...then none of us are gonna
be able to do our jobs.

556
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:11,078
And if we had lost
that little girl tonight...

557
00:38:12,120 --> 00:38:13,109
But we didn't.

558
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:15,388
But we could have.

559
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:20,388
And I don't think
I could live with that.

560
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:25,710
If that means that
I have to give up Leo...

561
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:32,197
...then I guess that's a sacrifice
I'm willing to make.

562
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:55,192
- Am I dreaming?
- No.

563
00:39:00,560 --> 00:39:02,596
I had a dream that you weren't
coming back.

564
00:39:07,280 --> 00:39:08,872
That wasn't a dream either, was it?

565
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:10,759
No, it wasn't.

566
00:39:12,440 --> 00:39:14,715
They had forbidden me
from ever seeing you again.

567
00:39:15,360 --> 00:39:16,952
But now...

568
00:39:17,720 --> 00:39:21,076
I don't know what you said or did,

569
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:24,915
but they said you showed
great courage and great faith.

570
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:27,429
Enough to make them reconsider.

571
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:29,795
Does that mean you guys
could get married now?

572
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:31,598
What? I wanna know.

573
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:36,873
Not yet. It means they're giving us a
chance to prove we can make it work.

574
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:39,034
What do you mean, like probation?

575
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:42,950
Well, if we can show them
that our relationship

576
00:39:43,120 --> 00:39:44,792
won't get in the way of our work...

577
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:46,274
Then we can stay together.

578
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:48,038
Right. But if anything goes wrong,

579
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:52,035
if we're distracted by each other
to the detriment of a single innocent...

580
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:53,633
We won't be.

581
00:40:04,720 --> 00:40:07,439
- Are you worried?
- When are you going to learn?

582
00:40:07,600 --> 00:40:08,874
I'm always worried.

583
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:12,672
I'm relieved that he's back though.
I mean not only for Piper but...

584
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:16,071
I know. Unknown unattractive
demon on the loose.

585
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:17,633
Let's not tell them till tomorrow.

586
00:40:17,840 --> 00:40:19,512
I think that
the least that they deserve

587
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:22,148
is one night worry-free romance,
don't you?

588
00:40:23,440 --> 00:40:25,431
Romance.

589
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:33,193
Turner.

590
00:40:34,200 --> 00:40:35,792
Hi. Cole.

591
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:39,157
What are you doing in the office
at 2 in the morning?

592
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:41,595
What are you doing calling my office
at 2 in the morning?

593
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:45,870
I was just gonna
leave you a message.

594
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:48,349
Save you the trouble
of having to talk to me.

595
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:50,352
Why would I ever
not wanna talk to you?

596
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:52,476
l... I don't know, you know.

597
00:40:52,680 --> 00:40:54,750
Just in case you thought I was
a drunk or a lunatic

598
00:40:54,920 --> 00:40:57,480
or a drunk lunatic.

599
00:40:57,680 --> 00:40:59,113
I think I'm gonna go with "mystery."

600
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:01,111
One I'm looking forward
to figuring out.

601
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:03,073
Okay.

602
00:41:04,360 --> 00:41:08,319
I'm gonna go then
and be mysterious.

603
00:41:09,160 --> 00:41:12,755
- I'll call you.
- I will answer.

604
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:19,232
Yes.

605
00:41:19,720 --> 00:41:22,280
Tell them I'm getting closer.

